# =============================================================================
# gitty — Christian Muehlhaeuser's "Contextual information about
#         your git projects, right on the command-line" — a Go
#         CLI that connects to GitHub/GitLab/Codeberg/Gitea
#         instances and displays a richly-formatted summary of a
#         repository: stars, watchers, last-release version,
#         active branches with commit/author info, recent commits,
#         open issues, open pull requests.  Distinguishing from
#         `gh repo view`, `gh pr list`, `gh issue list`,
#         glab/lab/forgejo-cli, and other forge clients by:
#           - SINGLE-COMMAND OVERVIEW — invoking `gitty` in a
#             git repo (or `gitty owner/repo` from anywhere)
#             produces a one-screen status panel with all
#             relevant info color-coded by lipgloss
#           - MULTI-FORGE: auto-detects GitHub / GitLab / Gitea /
#             Codeberg / Forgejo from the git remote URL +
#             dispatches to the appropriate API client
#           - ACTIVE BRANCHES with --max-branch-age filter
#             (default 28 days) — shows only branches with
#             recent commits, sorted by recency
#           - --skip-stale-repos for `--all-projects` mode that
#             scans an org's repos and shows only those with
#             new commits within --min-new-commits threshold
#           - ISSUE/PR URL JUMPING: `gitty 1234` (single
#             positional integer) opens issue or PR 1234 in
#             default browser
#           - REFLOW-TRUNCATED commit messages + PR titles +
#             issue titles — every long line truncated to
#             terminal width via muesli/reflow's truncate
#             module (ANSI-aware, wide-char-aware)
#           - LIPGLOSS THEMING with terminal-color-detected
#             palette (16-color / 256-color / TrueColor)
#         Used by: git users wanting fast at-a-glance project
#         status without leaving the terminal, contractors
#         scanning their open work across multiple repos,
#         maintainers reviewing recent activity across their
#         org's projects.
#
# Author:  Christian Muehlhaeuser (muesli on GitHub) — German
#          open-source developer, prolific Go contributor.
#          AUTHOR OF MUESLI/REFLOW (the headline library being
#          documented) AND co-maintainer of the Charm ecosystem
#          (charmbracelet/bubbletea, charmbracelet/lipgloss,
#          charmbracelet/glow, charmbracelet/soft-serve).
#          gitty released 2021; continuous development.
# Source:  https://github.com/muesli/gitty
#          https://github.com/muesli/gitty/blob/master/main.go
#          https://github.com/muesli/gitty/blob/master/commit.go
