#             1. SIX-MODULE ARCHITECTURE — reflow is organized
#              into independent sub-packages, each addressing
#              ONE wrapping concern:
#                * reflow/ansi — ANSI escape sequence handling
#                * reflow/dedent — strip common leading
#                  whitespace
#                * reflow/indent — add indent to each line
#                * reflow/padding — pad each line to width
#                * reflow/truncate — truncate to width with
#                  optional ellipsis
#                * reflow/wordwrap — break at word boundaries
#                * reflow/wrap — break at any character (hard
#                  wrap)
#             2. ALL MODULES ARE io.Writer IMPLEMENTATIONS —
#                each sub-package exposes a Writer type that
#                accepts written bytes and emits reformatted
#                output to an underlying io.Writer.  This
#                io.Writer compositional model means reflow
#                modules CHAIN naturally:
#                  out := wordwrap.NewWriter(80)
#                  indent.NewWriterPipe(out, 4, nil)
#                — works as a Decorator pattern across modules
#             3. ANSI-AWARE BY DEFAULT — every reflow module
