#                handling colored/styled terminal output
#             4. CHARM ECOSYSTEM CITIZEN — designed for use
#                with charmbracelet/bubbletea (TUI framework),
#                charmbracelet/lipgloss (styling), charmbracelet/
#                glow (markdown renderer), charmbracelet/soft-
#                serve (Git server)
#             5. TRUNCATE WITH ELLIPSIS — truncate.NewWriter(
#                width, "…") creates a writer that truncates
#                with custom suffix; widely used in TUI table
#                rendering for column-width-respecting cells
#             6. NEWPIPE COMPOSITION — every reflow module
#                provides NewWriter(args) AND NewWriterPipe(
#                upstream io.Writer, args) — letting users
#                compose writers in a pipeline with the
#                upstream parameter
#             7. STRING() CONVENIENCE — sibling String()
#                helpers (wordwrap.String(s, n), indent.String(
#                s, n)) avoid Writer boilerplate for one-shot
#                operations on existing strings)
